defs.docs: Brotli Compression/Decompression for Rust

defs.name: raw
defs.docs: Raw interface to in-memory compression/decompression streams

defs.name: Decompress
defs.docs: In-memory state for decompressing brotli-encoded data.

defs.name: Compress
defs.docs: In-memory state for compressing/encoding data with brotli

defs.name: Process
defs.docs: Compress input data

defs.name: Flush
defs.docs:
Compress input data, ensuring that all input so far has been
 written out

defs.name: Finish
defs.docs:
Compress input data, ensuring that all input so far has been
 written out and then finalizing the stream so no more data can
 be written

defs.name: EmitMetadata
defs.docs:
Emit a metadata block to the stream, an opaque piece of out-of-band
 data that does not interfere with the main stream of data. Metadata
 blocks *must* be no longer than 16MiB

defs.name: CompressOp
defs.docs: Possible choices for the operation performed by the compressor.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: Error that can happen from decompressing or compressing a brotli stream.

defs.name: Finished
defs.docs: The operation completed successfully

defs.name: Unfinished
defs.docs:
The operation has more work to do and needs to be called again with the
 same buffer

defs.name: CoStatus
defs.docs:
Indication of whether a compression operation is 'complete'. This does
 not indicate whether the whole stream is complete - see `Compress::compress`
 for details.

defs.name: Finished
defs.docs: Decompression was successful and has finished

defs.name: NeedInput
defs.docs: More input is needed to continue

defs.name: NeedOutput
defs.docs: More output is needed to continue

defs.name: DeStatus
defs.docs: Possible status results returned from decompressing.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a new brotli decompression/decoding stream ready to receive
 data.

defs.name: decompress
defs.value: fn (&mut self, input: &mut &[u8], output: &mut &mut [u8]) -> Result<DeStatus, Error>
defs.docs: Decompress some input data and write it to a buffer of output data.

defs.name: take_output
defs.docs:
Retrieve a slice of the internal decompressor buffer up to `size_limit` in length
 (unlimited length if `None`), consuming it. As the internal buffer may not be
 contiguous, consecutive calls may return more output until this function returns
 `None`.

defs.name: decompress_buf
defs.docs: Decompress data in one go in memory.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new compressor ready to encode data into brotli

defs.name: compress
defs.value: fn (&mut self, op: CompressOp, input: &mut &[u8], output: &mut &mut [u8]) -> Result<CoStatus, Error>
defs.docs:
Pass some input data to the compressor and write it to a buffer of
 output data, compressing or otherwise handling it as instructed by
 the specified operation.

defs.name: take_output
defs.docs:
Retrieve a slice of the internal compressor buffer up to `size_limit` in length
 (unlimited length if `None`), consuming it. As the internal buffer may not be
 contiguous, consecutive calls may return more output until this function returns
 `None`.
